```
// package.json scripts
"jest": "BABEL_ENV=jestTest jest",
"jest:coverage": "npm run jest -- --coverage"
```

```
// get coverage on one specific file
npm run jest -- --coverage [path/to/file]

// watch one specific file
npm run jest -- --watch --coverage [path/to/file]
```

VS (using plugin to view coverage in the .js or .jsx file after running `coverage` on the .spex.js file:
https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ryanluker.vscode-coverage-gutters)

NOT SURE IF THIS IS STILL VALID:
NOTE: the html coverage report may contain errors. This is because we currently use the babel reqire plugin which is not compatible with nyc (jest uses this tool for coverage).

